        <mxCell id="ErjgTOEo9CrdRjz5BF8E-8" value="&lt;h1&gt;Legend&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;On the left are action descriptors. They describe structure of json files bounded to specific actions. On the top, &quot;vibe_check&quot;, is an example of generic json file. All json files will have at least those three fields. These generic actions only tell the other side the type of action, nothing more. Specific json are described below &quot;vibe_check&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;On the right is described API between server and client, showed in &lt;font color=&quot;#ff3c26&quot;&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;&quot;&gt;SIDE-ACTION&lt;/i&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;format:&lt;br&gt;- Side says who&#39;s author of the action&lt;br&gt;- Action is on of the actions on the left.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If table is missing, this means it&#39;s a generic action, where action&#39;s name is its status.&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;spacing=5;spacingTop=-20;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
